JOHANNESBURG - Former president Jacob Zuma is still hospitalised at the Estcourt correctional centre following a surgical procedure on Saturday. ALSO READ:- Former President Jacob Zuma admitted to hospital- State says doctor's letter doesn't identify Jacob Zuma's medical condition Zuma had been serving a 15-month jail sentence for contempt of court following his failure to appear at the state capture inquiry. The Department of Correctional Services said it did not know when he would be discharged and that he was scheduled for other procedures. The department’s Singabakho Nxumalo said, “We appeal to all people to refrain from speculating on the health of Mr Zuma and allow medical practitioners space to continue providing quality healthcare to him.” Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android  device.